OL,3,CMan's recovery in 1923 declared first
OL,4,CEnglish miracle
OL,6,FITV Granada Reports correspondent Rob
OL,7,FSmith was at the mass where the case
OL,8,Fof John Traynor was declared a miracle
OL,10,FThe sudden recovery of a man with
OL,11,Fepilepsy has been declared a miracle
OL,12,Fby the Archbishop of Liverpool Malcolm
OL,13,FMcMahon OP - making it the first
OL,14,FEnglish case to be recognised.
OL,16,FJohn (Jack) Traynor, from Merseyside,
OL,17,Fwas cured of epilepsy, paralysis of
OL,18,Fthe right arm and paraplegia while
OL,19,Ftaking part in the archdiocese's first
OL,20,Fofficial pilgrimage to Lourdes in 1923
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/8
